    <note caller="[g]" style="f">
      <char style="fk">[g]</char>
      <char style="ft"><char style="it">add a minute to your lifespan</char>…Lit: <char style="it">add a cubit to his lifespan</char>.
        Applying cubits, a unit of length, to lifespans, measured in time, is idiomatic. This is similar to the
        use of the word <char style="it">inch</char>, a unit of length,<char style="it"> </char>in the idiom
        <char style="it">within an inch of his life</char>, like in: <char style="it">he had been beaten to within
