    </note>
    <note caller="[A]" style="f">
      <char style="fk">[A]</char>
      <char style="ft"><char style="it">A certain man planted a vineyard</char>…Jesus’s parable of the vineyard here is actually
        a variation of the parable in Isaiah 5:1–7. The Scribes and chief priests were caught up in the telling
        of the parable (v. 16 <char style="it">Heaven forbid!</char>), instead of thinking on their feet and
        recollecting the theme of Isaiah’s original parable, which they would’ve surely been familiar with.</char>
    </note>
    <note caller="[B]" style="f">
      <char style="fk">[B]</char>
      <char style="ft"><char style="it">Everyone falling upon that stone will be crumbled; whoever it happens to fall on, it
        will pulverize</char>…Ref. note of Matt. 21:44</char>
    </note>
    <note caller="[C]" style="f">
      <char style="fk">[C]</char>
      <char style="ft"><char style="it">coin (a denarius)</char>…Lit: <char style="it">denarius</char>. This was a Roman coin.
        The Jews were forced to use currencies from other nations, but in so doing were benefitting from the
        Roman system which supported the currency. As beneficiaries of this system, they were obligated to support
        it through taxation, the point that Jesus makes. In their hypocrisy, they were reaping the benefit but
        despising the system bestowing it.</char>
    </note>
  <chapter eid="LUK 20" />
  <!--   **********   -->
  <!--   Chapter 21   -->
  <!--   **********   -->
  <chapter number="21" style="c" sid="LUK 21" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="LUK 21:1" />He looked up and saw the rich laying their offerings on the offering plate<char style="sup">[a]</char><verse eid="LUK 21:1" />
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="LUK 21:2" />and saw a widow there who was poor put in two dollars<char style="sup">[A]</char>, <verse eid="LUK 21:2" />
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="LUK 21:3" />and said, <char style="wj">“I’m telling you the truth—this poor widow by herself contributed more than
        all of the others </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">combined</char></char><char style="wj">. </char><verse eid="LUK 21:3" />
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="LUK 21:4" /><char style="wj">You see, all of these people contributed out of their abundance; she, however, out of
        her lack contributed everything she has to live on.”</char><verse eid="LUK 21:4" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="LUK 21:5" />While a few people were talking about the temple, <char style="it">the fact </char>that with pledge-offerings
        it had been adorned in beautiful stones, he said, <verse eid="LUK 21:5" />
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="LUK 21:6" /><char style="wj">”These </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">things </char></char><char style="wj">that
        you see here: there’s coming a day in which a </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">single</char></char><char
        style="wj"> stone won’t be left stacked on top of </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">another</char></char><char
        style="wj"> stone, which hasn’t been torn down.”</char><verse eid="LUK 21:6" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="LUK 21:7" />So they asked him, “So now, teacher, when will these things take place? And what will be the <char style="it">supernatural</char>
        sign when these things are about to happen?” <verse eid="LUK 21:7" />
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="LUK 21:8" />He said, <char style="wj">“See to it that you’re not led in the wrong direction. You see, many will come
        claiming to have my authority</char><char style="sup">[B]</char><char style="wj"> saying, ‘I am </char><char
        style="it"><char style="wj">the one-and-only one</char></char><char style="sup">[b]</char><char style="wj">,’
        and, ‘The timeframe is right around the corner</char><char style="sup">[c]</char><char style="wj">.’
        Don’t go follow after them. </char><verse eid="LUK 21:8" />
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="LUK 21:9" /><char style="wj">When you hear about wars, conflicts, and revolutions, don’t be terrified: you see, these
        things have to happen beforehand. No, the end is not imminent.”</char><verse eid="LUK 21:9" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="LUK 21:10" />Then he kept on talking telling them, <char style="wj">“Nation will be mobilized in hostility against
        nation, ethnic group against ethnic group, and kingdom against kingdom, </char><verse eid="LUK 21:10" />
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="LUK 21:11" /><char style="wj">plus there’ll be enormous earthquakes and famines &amp; plagues</char><char style="sup">[C]</char><char
        style="wj"> from place to place. There’ll be terrors, and not just terrors but great portents, signs
        sent from heaven appearing in the sky.</char><verse eid="LUK 21:11" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="LUK 21:12" /><char style="wj">”But before all these </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">things happen</char></char><char
        style="wj">, they’ll get their clutches on you and prosecute you, delivering you to the synagogues and
        jails, being led away to </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">appear before</char></char><char style="wj">
        kings and governors on account of you acting as directed by me</char><char style="sup">[d]</char><char
        style="wj">. </char><verse eid="LUK 21:12" />
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="LUK 21:13" /><char style="wj">Circumstances will result in </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">an opportunity</char></char><char
        style="wj"> for you to testify. </char><verse eid="LUK 21:13" />
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="LUK 21:14" /><char style="wj">So now, settle it in your hearts not to rehearse what you’ll say in defense; </char><verse eid="LUK 21:14" />
      <verse number="15" style="v" sid="LUK 21:15" /><char style="wj">for I personally will give you rhetoric</char><char style="sup">[e]</char><char style="wj">
        and wisdom which </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">your opponents</char></char><char style="wj">
        won’t be able to put forth a rebuttal against or refute. </char><verse eid="LUK 21:15" />
      <verse number="16" style="v" sid="LUK 21:16" /><char style="wj">You’ll be betrayed by parents and brothers and relatives and friends, and they’ll kill
        others from among you, </char><verse eid="LUK 21:16" />
      <verse number="17" style="v" sid="LUK 21:17" /><char style="wj">and you’ll be hated by everyone because of everything I stand for. </char><verse eid="LUK 21:17" />
      <verse number="18" style="v" sid="LUK 21:18" /><char style="wj">But not a single hair on your head will be lost—not one. </char><verse eid="LUK 21:18" />
      <verse number="19" style="v" sid="LUK 21:19" /><char style="wj">By your perseverance you will stay in control of your lives.</char><verse eid="LUK 21:19" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="20" style="v" sid="LUK 21:20" /><char style="wj">”When you see Jerusalem surrounded by an army encampment, at that moment know that its
        devastation is right around the corner. </char><verse eid="LUK 21:20" />
      <verse number="21" style="v" sid="LUK 21:21" /><char style="wj">At that moment, those in Judea: flee to the mountains; those </char><char style="it"><char
        style="wj">caught</char></char><char style="wj"> in the center of it, </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">that
        is Judea</char></char><char style="wj">: get out; those in the surrounding areas: don’t enter </char><char
        style="it"><char style="wj">the area</char></char><char style="wj">, </char><verse eid="LUK 21:21" />
      <verse number="22" style="v" sid="LUK 21:22" /><char style="wj">because it’s pay-back time, the day of reckoning, the fulfillment of everything recorded
        in the Scriptures. </char><verse eid="LUK 21:22" />
      <verse number="23" style="v" sid="LUK 21:23" /><char style="wj">Bad news</char><char style="sup">[f]</char><char style="wj"> for pregnant women when
        those days come around and for women who are breast feeding, as everything all over the place will be
        in really short supply and </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">what with</char></char><char style="wj">
        wrath </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">being dished out </char></char><char style="wj">on this
        </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">nation of </char></char><char style="wj">people. </char><verse eid="LUK 21:23" />
      <verse number="24" style="v" sid="LUK 21:24" /><char style="wj">They’ll fall by the edge of the sword, and they’ll be led into captivity to all the
        </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">Gentile </char></char><char style="wj">nations, and Jerusalem
        will be utterly dominated and disrespected</char><char style="sup">[g]</char><char style="wj"> by the
        Gentiles, until such a time as the Gentile’s </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">allotted</char></char><char
        style="wj"> timeframe</char><char style="sup">[h]</char><char style="wj"> run its course</char><char
        style="sup">[i]</char><char style="wj">.</char><verse eid="LUK 21:24" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="25" style="v" sid="LUK 21:25" /><char style="wj">”And the sun, moon, and stars will be used for supernatural</char><char style="it"><char
        style="wj"> </char></char><char style="wj">signs, while on earth there’ll be anguish and anxiety of nations
        and peoples all over the world, a clamor of the waves and the sea</char><char style="sup">[D]</char><char
        style="wj"> in perplexity and dismay, </char><verse eid="LUK 21:25" />
      <verse number="26" style="v" sid="LUK 21:26" /><char style="wj">men fainting from the fear and the suspense of those things coming to—being imposed
        on—the inhabited world; for the laws of physics that govern the sky above and the universe beyond will
        be perturbed</char><char style="sup">[j]</char><char style="wj">. </char><verse eid="LUK 21:26" />
      <verse number="27" style="v" sid="LUK 21:27" /><char style="wj">At that time they’ll see ’the Man</char><char style="sup">[k]</char><char style="wj">
        coming in a cloud’ with much power and glory. </char><verse eid="LUK 21:27" />
      <verse number="28" style="v" sid="LUK 21:28" /><char style="wj">While these things are coming to pass, pull yourselves together and lift your spirits</char><char
        style="sup">[E]</char><char style="wj">, because your having things restored for you and your having
        things put back to the way they’re supposed to be for you is just around the corner</char><char style="sup">[l]</char><char
        style="wj">.”</char><verse eid="LUK 21:28" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="29" style="v" sid="LUK 21:29" /><char style="wj">So he told them an analogy, “Observe the fig tree and </char><char style="it"><char
        style="wj">for that matter </char></char><char style="wj">all the trees. </char><verse eid="LUK 21:29" />
      <verse number="30" style="v" sid="LUK 21:30" /><char style="wj">By the time it should have put out </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">its shoots</char></char><char
        style="wj"> already, see for yourselves and understand that the time is already near for the harvest.
        </char><verse eid="LUK 21:30" />
      <verse number="31" style="v" sid="LUK 21:31" /><char style="wj">In this way you too, when you see these thinks happening, know that God’s involvement
        with mankind (God’s kingdom) is near. </char><verse eid="LUK 21:31" />
      <verse number="32" style="v" sid="LUK 21:32" /><char style="wj">I’m telling you the honest-to-goodness truth—this self-same generation</char><char style="sup">[m]</char><char
        style="wj"> won’t pass away until everything comes to pass. </char><verse eid="LUK 21:32" />
      <verse number="33" style="v" sid="LUK 21:33" /><char style="wj">The sky and the earth will grow old and fade out of existence</char><char style="sup">[n]</char><char
        style="wj">, but these words of mine will in no way whatsoever grow old and fade into irrelevance</char><char
        style="sup">[n]</char><char style="wj">.</char><verse eid="LUK 21:33" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="34" style="v" sid="LUK 21:34" /><char style="wj">”Pay attention to yourselves, lest your hearts become lethargic, weighed down by binge
        drinking and drunkenness and by the anxieties of every-day life, and these days come all of a sudden
        and relentlessly oppress you</char><char style="sup">[o]</char><char style="wj">, </char><verse eid="LUK 21:34" />
      <verse number="35" style="v" sid="LUK 21:35" /><char style="wj">like a snare </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">trapping an animal</char></char><char
        style="wj">. You see, these days will come oppressively upon</char><char style="sup">[o]</char><char
        style="wj"> all people everywhere all over the planet, those simply relaxing and keeping to themselves</char><char
        style="sup">[p]</char><char style="wj">. </char><verse eid="LUK 21:35" />
      <verse number="36" style="v" sid="LUK 21:36" /><char style="wj">Be on the lookout in all the various circumstances of life and in the change in current
        events</char><char style="sup">[q]</char><char style="wj">, praying all the while so that you would come
        out on top in your fleeing away from all these things which are going to happen, and </char><char style="it"><char
        style="wj">that you would</char></char><char style="wj"> stand before the Man.”</char><verse eid="LUK 21:36" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="37" style="v" sid="LUK 21:37" />He was teaching in the temple during the day, but he was leaving <char style="it">the city </char>and
        spending the night on the large hill called <char style="it">the Mount of</char> Olives. <verse eid="LUK 21:37" />
      <verse number="38" style="v" sid="LUK 21:38" />And all the folk were getting up early each morning to listen to him in the temple.<verse eid="LUK 21:38" />
    </para>
